Villarreal of Spain’s attacker, Samuel Chukwueze, arrived at the Super Eagles camp yesterday morning to increase the number of players in camp to 25 as the team departed the country for Cameroon. The Spanish side delayed the release of the Super Eagles winger to the Nigeria Football Federation until after January 3 as the 22-year-old was instrumental, providing an assist, in the Yellow-Submarines’ emphatic 5-0 win over Levante at the El Madrigal on Monday.   BetKing to fly five fans to watch AFCON finals     Covid chaos stop Senegal flight to Cameroon     Salah issues AFCON battle cry   The 2015 U17 world cup winner was on for 73 minutes before being substituted by Spanish wonderkid Yeremi Pino. As they look forward to win their fourth African title and first in nine years, the Super Eagles on-board a chartered flight at 8pm last night depart Nnamdi Azikiwe International Airport, Abuja for Garoua where they would begin their campaign against the Pharaohs of Egypt on January 11.The Super Eagles are in group D of the AFCON alongside Egypt, Sudan and Guinea-Bissau. Meanwhile, as the team were departing for Cameroon, the president of NFF, Amaju Pinnick, represented by NFF’s Secretary general Dr. Muhammed Sanusi told the team to make the country proud and assured the team that the NFF would ensure that all their needs are met.